        <div type="recipe">
        <p> Take four Lemmons, rasp the Rinds into a Pint and half of Spring-Water, let it lye an Hour; and then put to it the Whites of five Eggs well beaten, half a Pound of Sugar, and the Juice of four Lemmons; when the Sugar is melted, strain it thro ’ a thin Sieve or Strainer; then take a little Powder of Turmerick, ty ’ d up in a Piece of Muslin, and lay it in a Spoonful of Water ’ till it is wet; then squeeze a little into the Jelly, to make it Lemmon-Colour, but not too Yellow : Set it over the Fire, skim it, and when you see it jelly, put it in Glasses; if it boil, it will not be amiss. </p>
            </div>
